### Prior history for myrmidon-swarm-end-to-end-orchestration-full-workflow

## v1.7.0 (2026-05-18)

**Changed by:** 2026-05-18 skill-corpus consolidation (17 clusters, 1,100→690 skills); Mojo mega-cluster split session
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed
- Added new subsection `### Variant: per-namespace sequential dispatch (intra-cluster split)` under Verified Workflow
- Added 1 new Failed Attempts row: parallel dispatch on shared `mojo-*` namespace (sub-PRs #1808-#1811)
- Added Verified On row: HomericIntelligence/ProjectMnemosyne 2026-05-18 consolidation, tracking issue #1813
- Bumped version 1.6.0 → 1.7.0; updated date to 2026-05-18

### Why
Running a 114-member Mojo mega-cluster as a single PR was infeasible. Splitting into 4 sub-PRs
by theme was required. Attempting parallel dispatch on the shared `mojo-*` namespace would have
caused race conditions on branch refs and auto-merge cascade rebases. Sequential dispatch took
~50 min for all 4 sub-PRs with zero conflicts. Pattern is reusable for any cluster with a
shared filename prefix.

